<subSubSection pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,476,501]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Latin adjective “ 
<emphasis box="[639,693,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">latus</emphasis>
”, meaning broad, and noun “ 
<emphasis box="[1028,1088,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">lobus</emphasis>
”, meaning hull or husk, thus a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
